This is a documentation-only patch. The actual fix is implemented directly
in the PKGBUILD package() function by creating fake-bin/uname wrapper.

Problem: jtagserver runs "uname -p" which returns "unknown" on modern
Linux kernels (CachyOS, Arch, etc.) instead of "x86_64". This breaks
the WINUSB/GWU2U cable type's architecture detection.

Fix: A wrapper script at /opt/gowin-eda-programmer/fake-bin/uname
intercepts "uname -p" and returns "x86_64", delegating all other
flags to the real /usr/bin/uname.
